     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
================================================ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">A prestigious western enclave with large blocks, river aspect, and the kind of space that upsizing families travel from across Brisbane to find.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Fig Tree Pocket sits approximately eleven kilometres west of the Brisbane CBD in a bend of the Brisbane River, occupying a position in the western corridor that has earned it a reputation as one of the city's more distinctive residential enclaves. The suburb is defined by generous blocks, established native vegetation, a mix of large modern family homes and older properties on spacious lots, and in parts a river aspect that is genuinely rare at this distance from the CBD. The buyers who choose Fig Tree Pocket are not making a compromise on location to gain space: they have decided that space, privacy, and the suburb's western enclave character are precisely what they want, and they have moved through a deliberate decision-making process to arrive at this conclusion.
    </p>
