<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:40px 24px 80px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">FAQ</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Common questions about Fig Tree Pocket.</h2>
    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Fig Tree Pocket?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Block size, river aspect, privacy and scarcity are the primary value drivers in Fig Tree Pocket. The combination of generous lots, established vegetation and the suburb's western enclave character is genuinely difficult to replicate in neighbouring suburbs at the same price point. Low turnover means buyers often wait specifically for a Fig Tree Pocket property to appear, and that committed buyer intent translates to stronger competition when the right home is presented correctly.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Fig Tree Pocket?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Fig Tree Pocket homes typically sell within 25 to 45 days. The active buyer pool is smaller than in a mass-market suburb, but it is highly committed and well-informed: buyers who have been watching the suburb know what properties are worth, and the right campaign at the right price will attract meaningful competition. Accurate pricing is more important here than in suburbs where a larger buyer pool can absorb minor mispricing.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Fig Tree Pocket?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Fig Tree Pocket offers a private, spacious lifestyle in the western Brisbane corridor, with generous blocks, native bush character and the river aspect that parts of the suburb enjoy. Everyday amenity comes from the Kenmore corridor, and the Indooroopilly Shopping Centre provides broader retail. It is a suburb for families who are buying space and privacy as deliberately as they are buying a house, and the lifestyle reflects that intent.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Fig Tree Pocket a good suburb to buy in right now?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Fig Tree Pocket is one of western Brisbane's more tightly held addresses, and the scarcity that characterises the market has historically supported sound price performance. For buyers who have concluded that block size, privacy and a western Brisbane lifestyle are the right fit for the next stage of their lives, Fig Tree Pocket remains a compelling and genuinely scarce option. The suburb is not for buyers who are still weighing up their priorities; it is for those who have already decided.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

